Santam suffered a 41% drop in full-year headline earnings per share (HEPS) to R10.86, hit by low investment results and lower underwriting profits. Investment income dropped to R832m in the year to December, from R1.44bn in the year-earlier period. Foreign-currency exchange losses had a significant negative effect on investment returns, offsetting the investment portfolio performance at home. The short-term insurer suffered R372m in forex losses, from R467m gain in the year-earlier period, as the rand appreciated 12% against the dollar. A few large, corporate property claims and drought-related claims affected the underwriting results. The crop insurance business achieved a net underwriting profit of R69m, down from R131m in the year-earlier period, as a result of drought-related claims.